close_reason: Fixed native Windows command hint quoting and pinned the regression in required CI.
body: "Nightly Validation windows-latest / Node 24 red since 2026-07-11 (GH-522 filed off the 2026-07-12 run 29182914361 on c7b56e73; the 07-11 leg failed identically but was masked by the macOS pm-dprb failure fixed in PR#520).\n\nBisect (clean): 07-10 nightly green on 1bdca537 (pre-PR#491); PR#491 (b5a41fba, merged 2026-07-10 10:25) introduced buildInitNextSteps pm-path scoping — every scoped hint renders through renderPmCommand → quoteCommandArg (src/cli/argv-utils.ts:41).\n\nRoot cause: quoteCommandArg's safe charset `[A-Za-z0-9._:/@=-]` omits backslash, and its escaper doubles `\\`. Any native Windows tracker path (e.g. C:\\tmp\\tracker) therefore renders as `--pm-path \"C:\\\\tmp\\\\tracker\"`. This is a PRODUCT defect, not just a spec mismatch: the copy-paste hint is POSIX-shell quoting shown to cmd/PowerShell users — doubled backslashes are a literal wrong path there.\n\nFailing specs (windows-only, deterministic): tests/unit/commands/init-command.spec.ts (covers init option normalizers / normalized prefix / preset registration / guidance status — all assert bare `${path.resolve(...)}` in hints) + tests/integration/init-path-guard.integration.spec.ts (path-like positional guard).\n\nFix direction (code-side, NOT spec-side — pm-gf6f precedent shows spec-only fixes let the class recur): platform-aware quoting — on win32 quote only when the arg needs it and never backslash-escape path separators (cmd/PowerShell rules); keep POSIX behavior (incl. the `$`-escaping the replacement-sensitive spec pins) unchanged. Alternative (admitting `\\` to the safe charset) breaks paths with spaces and mis-escapes inside quotes — rejected.\n\nOracle gap: PR CI's windows-regression job does not run these suites, so nightly is the sole oracle for this class (same gap shape as pm-dprb/GH-510 on macOS)."
